org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.ace

Interface AceContig

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Contig<AceAssembledRead>

    public interface AceContig
extends Contig<AceAssembledRead>
    an AceContig is a Contig from an ace file. Each AceContig is made up of AceAssembledReads.

      • getReadIterator

        StreamingIterator<AceAssembledRead> getReadIterator()
        The order of the reads returned by this iterator is ordered by AssembledRead.getGappedStartOffset(). If two reads have the same start offset, then the shorter read determined by AssembledRead.getGappedLength() is returned. If two reads have the same start offset AND gapped length, the the read with the lexigraphically lower read id is returned.

        Get the StreamingIterator of AssembledReads that are contained in this contig.

        Specified by:
        getReadIterator in interface Contig<AceAssembledRead>
        Returns:
        a StreamingIterator of AssembledReads; will never be null and never contain any null elements, but could be empty.
